blue: having the colour of a clear sky or the sea on a clear day
alloy: a metal that is formed by mixing two types of metal together, or by mixing metal with another substance
autonomous: able to govern itself or control its own affairs
control: the power to make decisions about how a country, an area, an organization, etc.
vacation: a period of time spent travelling or resting away from home
observation: the act of watching somebody/something carefully for a period of time, especially to learn something
possibility: a thing that may happen or be true; the fact that something might happen or be true, but is not certain
adjudication: the process of making an official decision about who is right when two groups or organizations disagree; the decision that is mad
buoyancy: a situation in which prices, business activity, etc. tend to increase or stay at a high level, usually showing financial success
love: a very strong feeling of liking and caring for somebody/something, especially a member of your family or a frieeeeend
accountability: the fact of being responsible for your decisions or actions and expected to explain them when you are asked
nature: all the plants, animals and things that exist in the universe that are not made by people
coalition: a government formed by two or more political parties working together
baby: a very young child or animal
wild: living or growing in natural conditions; not kept in a house or on a farm
little: not big; small; smaller than others
bite: to use your teeth to cut into or through something
